Purchased and used 4 packs, no issues. For my children's birthday party we made "mixed tapes" with 10 songs on them as party favors. We made 75 total, and not 1 of them had an issue. These were super affordable and perfect for this small project. There are comments about them not holding much, which I suppose is true, but that is because they are only 64mb (per product description). You can find guideline charts online about how much mb/GB common projects are, which is helpful before selecting the right size USB as file size needed is not always intuitive. SMALL storage capacity. Don't confuse MB with GB but I just need some small ones to hold some small files (for embroidery) and these fit the bill. I like how you can easily write on them with a sharpie Nifty. A little small but great for small projects. What customers think about Kepmem?

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars White elephant gifter’s dream
reviews.reviewText: These bad boys were *exactly* what I was looking for. Bulk, cheap, colorful … and absolutely useless for most people. The ones I tested worked perfectly and they actually had a really nice finish and weight to them, which was an unexpected bonus. I purchased the 64 Mb size, which is just about big enough for a word document. Maybe even TWO word documents. (Yes you read that right). Bahaha. Amazing.Grab a hundred, put a digital Amazon giftcard claim code on just one of them, add a note (i.e. “One of these devices has an Amazon giftcard on it. May the odds be ever in your favor”) and your passive-aggressive work holiday party white elephant gift is good to go for this year. Or do what I did and mix a few packs of these with conference USB devices, floppy disks and Zip disks.If I need bulk USB storage devices with a more usable capacity at some point, I would totally consider this company again based on the quality of the ones I received.

reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Nice nifty flash drives - great for loading a handful of songs on
reviews.reviewText: Technology can be a wonderful thing. My Dad makes cd's for his car to listen to when he drives, he even makes some cd's for his friends. Now that technology has advanced most cars don't have cd players anymore so my dad is unable to use his cd's with these vehicles.When I went home to visit I suggested he use flash drives. I ordered some and had shipped to him. I told him how to format and sync songs. He loves it. Only issue, the 128MB drives I sent he was only able to fit 14 songs on. I think 256MB would be better for him. He can fit 24-28 songs.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 5, 2021
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars good for the price->> but not 128MB
reviews.reviewText: I bought these to transfer music cd's onto.My idea was to put two or maybe 3 cd's onto a single flash drive.I bought the 128MB drives to do this. The drives I got were only 118MB. Still enough to do what I wanted to do but if I needed every bit of the 128MB I would have been out of luck.Many of my CD's are either side of 50MB each which leaves about 15 to 20MB available on the flash drive.Two large CD's or three small CD's wont go on these 118MB drives but possibly would have if a true 128MB flash drive was sent.Likely will buy more, but false or exaggerated specs is really getting annoying.
